The paper deals with planning under uncertainty in the presence of intermittent sensing, which is a common problem in robotics and autonomous systems. The focus is on state estimation and path planning, which are core topics in robotics and control. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category. The paper also involves analytical and computational methods for decision-making, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The examples given in the abstract involve camera systems and LIDAR sensors, which are related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
